Synchrony BC/PC application have two databases:
1) Portal DB 
2) Reporting DB

- Both DB have three instances for QA, UAT, Stage
- So, in total there are 6 instances
- Raise DB access request for all the 6 instances ---> Means User with your SSO ID will be created in each of the 6 instances and will be given access
- You will receive password for all the 6 instances
- Login to these 6 DB instances with Username(your SSO ID) and Password(received in mail)

EXAMPLE:
In Synchrony: I got a mail with 
Instance name: ptplqa01
Username: SSO ID
Password: xyz

- Open SQL Developer
- Click New Connection
- Enter below details:
  UserInfo:
  Username: 503030793
  Password: received in mail

  Connection Details:
  Hostname: vqlptrptldbda01.prvcld.syfbank.com (Ask lead which host to connect)
  Port: 1535 
  SID: ptplqa01  { Give the instance name to connect to (received in mail) 

- Test connection and Connect

